gomodel:SYNGO_303  a      owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Automated change 2024-03-14: GO:0030285 replaced by GO:0030672" , "Rationale: In this study, Brand et al. used subcellular fractionation and immunocytochemistry to localize SCAMP 1 (SCAMP 37). SCAMP1 colocalizes with synaptophysin (synaptic vesicle marker). However, in comparison to other synaptic vesicle marker proteins, SCAMP 1 is much more broadly distributed within neurons as immunoreactivity was also detected in cell bodies and dendrites of Purkinje cells.\n\n5/2/2018 PIm\n- Based on the known transmembrane topology of the protein, the \"integral component of ... membrane\" term was chosen.. Experimental description: Fractions enriched in synaptic vesicles derived from rat brain were further fractionated by velocity sedimentation on glycerol gradients." ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-3898-5197" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0808-7003" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-1542-3498" ;
        dc:date           "2024-03-14" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_303" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

